JUMUIYA WOMEN GROUP is a welfare group, registered in 2001 as a Community Based Organization (CBO) with an active program on advocacy and lobbying. It aims to achieve its goals through networking, civic education, training, research, advocacy, lobbying and information collection, packaging and exchange.  The group derives its strength from the diversity of expertise and experience of its membership and allies. It strives to articulate plurality, human rights, health, security, dignity, freedom, environmental protection, justice and peace for all people and open up democratic space for women’s organizations in North Rift from its base in Uasin- Gishu district, KENYA.

Hope for Suffering Humanity in Gojra Pakistan. The Christians there are currently suffering a severe shortage of food and clothing, basic human needs. Following the blasphemy laws introduced, they are marginalized and unable to find work to provide for their families. I would like to nominate them as a possible recipient of emergency funding and am already running a personal campaign to try and raise awareness of their specific needs.

The project intends to reach poor women and out of school youths without employement through apprentiship program where already established women and youth artisans/apprentice attach other women and youth to gain the same skills after which they are trained and mentored on basic entrepreneurship and then linked to micro lending institutions to loans to establish businesses. This way, the skill is passed from a woman to woman or from youth to youth at no cost which is also sustainable.

Create a livlihood/training center for women in Philippines: The center will provide skills that will help her family or herself earn income on their own or thru employment. One of the training would be cooking, sewing, handicrafts, manicure/pedicure etc. Women that falls on this category has also a chance to become a trainer, once she is trained she is required to train two women on the skills that she acquired in the training center then each women will also train two women until such time  that all women in the world has the capacity to contribute to the society.
